```julia
function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> isuppercase(word[1]), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` function from the Base module in Julia. It takes an anonymous function as the first argument, which checks if the first character of each word is uppercase using `isuppercase(word[1])`. The `filter` function keeps only the words for which this condition is true, effectively removing all words that do not start with a capital letter.
